author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. Government Bonds Rise on Haven Demand
text:
U.S. Treasury bonds strengthened Thursday as weaker global stocks boosted demand for haven assets.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note was 2.112%, according to Tradeweb, compared with 2.129% Wednesday, the lowest closing level since May 29.
